summary: I understand what you’re saying but florida is very big
question: I understand what you’re saying but florida is very big
answer:
I’m aware, but so is europe (a continent.. vs a state) and comparatively europe really didn’t have that many dates at all (not counting the uk). southern and eastern europe were entirely ignored, london and berlin sold out in 3 seconds and they only had one show each, not even a matinee show. the venue in berlin was small. many of the venues in america are twice as big as those in europe. canada is the second largest country in the world after russia, it’s an english speaking country, but it only has two shows. there are other big states in the us that have no shows at all, not to mention all the other countries in the world where they aren’t going.

what I’m trying to say is that this tour makes no sense to me and is also a bit unfair to a lot of people. and yes, I’m aware they couldn’t go everywhere, I’m aware they’re not to blame, I’m aware many issues probably had to do with venues’ availability, and don’t get me wrong, I hope everyone at the show tonight has the best time, but when I see people complaining that one of the 4 shows in florida didn’t sell well, I can’t help but being salty, because I know that elsewhere that same show would have sold out and made a lot of other people very happy.
